{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:27:26.252Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In classical machine learning, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-SNE (t-distributed Stochastic Neighbor Embedding)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a nonlinear dimensionality reduction technique used primarily to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "visualize high-dimensional data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " by embedding it into a 2D or 3D map while preserving local structure."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " “t-SNE is a statistical method for visualizing high-dimensional data by giving each datapoint a location in a two or three-dimensional map.”"}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "t-SNE — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What t-SNE is and why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Many ML datasets are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "high-dimensional"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": each sample has dozens, hundreds, or thousands of features (e.g., gene expression, image pixels, word embeddings). Humans can’t directly visualize that."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE helps by:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Taking "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "high-dimensional data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., 1000-dimensional gene profiles)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mapping it to a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "low-dimensional space"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (2D or 3D)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Placing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "similar points close together"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "dissimilar points far apart"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with high probability"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key idea: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Similar objects → nearby points; dissimilar objects → distant points"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How t-SNE works (conceptually)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE has "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "two main stages"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. High-dimensional probability distribution"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE computes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "pairwise similarities"}, {"type": "text", "text": " between points in the high-dimensional space, often using a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gaussian distribution"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It converts these similarities into "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "probabilities"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- High probability if two points are close (similar neighbors) - Low probability if they are far\n- This defines a probability distribution over pairs of high-dimensional points where similar points have higher probabilities"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Low-dimensional probability distribution + optimization"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE defines a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "similar probability distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": " over points in the low-dimensional map (2D/3D)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For the low-dimensional space, it uses a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Student t-distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (with one degree of freedom) instead of a Gaussian"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It then minimizes the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kullback–Leibler (KL) divergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": " between the high-dimensional and low-dimensional probability distributions by adjusting the positions of points in the map"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In simple terms:\n- t-SNE tries to make the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "low-dimensional map’s neighbor relationships"}, {"type": "text", "text": " match the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "high-dimensional data’s neighbor relationships"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as closely as possible."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key properties of t-SNE"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Nonlinear dimensionality reduction"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "nonlinear"}, {"type": "text", "text": " method, unlike PCA (Principal Component Analysis), which is linear."}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PCA"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": finds straight-line directions that maximize variance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-SNE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": can capture complex, curved manifolds and nonlinear structures"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This makes t-SNE especially good for:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cluster visualization"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Uncovering "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "local relationships"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that PCA misses"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Emphasis on local structure"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE focuses strongly on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "local neighborhoods"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It preserves which points are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "close neighbors"}, {"type": "text", "text": " very well"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It shows tight, clear "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "clusters"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "But it "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "distorts global structure"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "distances between clusters"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are not meaningful"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The spacing and arrangement of clusters in the plot may not reflect reality"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Key hyperparameter: perplexity"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE is tuned mainly by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "perplexity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", which roughly controls:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How many neighbors"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to consider when defining local neighborhoods"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical values: 5–50, depending on dataset size"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Higher perplexity → considers more neighbors → more global structure (but still limited). Lower perplexity → focuses on very local structure → many small clusters."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE in Classical Machine Learning (not Generative AI)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "classical machine learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", t-SNE is used as an "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "exploratory and visualization tool"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not as a core model for prediction."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common use cases:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visualizing clusters in:"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Single-cell RNA sequencing"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (gene expression data) - "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Image data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., MNIST digits) - "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Text embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (word vectors, document embeddings)\n- Exploring structure in: - High-dimensional "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "bioinformatics"}, {"type": "text", "text": " data - "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Flow cytometry"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "mass cytometry"}, {"type": "text", "text": " data\n- Understanding the behavior of: - Deep learning models (e.g., visualizing embeddings from neural networks)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "not typically used for prediction"}, {"type": "text", "text": "; it’s a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "visualization and analysis"}, {"type": "text", "text": " technique in classical ML workflows."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE vs. UMAP"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "UMAP (Uniform Manifold Approximation and Projection)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are both nonlinear dimensionality reduction methods for visualization that preserve local neighborhood structure."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Core differences"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "UMAP"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Speed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slow; computationally expensive"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Much faster; scales to millions of points"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Global structure"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Poor; distances between clusters are meaningless"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Preserves "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "somewhat more global structure"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output interpretation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Only local neighborhoods are trustworthy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Both local neighborhoods and some global geometry are more meaningful"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "New data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No out-of-sample transform; must recompute for new data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Supports "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "out-of-sample transform"}, {"type": "text", "text": "; can embed new points without recomputing everything"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss function"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "KL divergence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-entropy"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Philosophy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Probability matching (Gaussian in high-D, t-distribution in low-D)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Graph-based (constructs and preserves a k-NN graph)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-SNE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": excellent for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "tight local clusters"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and fine-grain structure"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "UMAP"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": better for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "real-world workflows"}, {"type": "text", "text": " because it’s faster, preserves more global structure, and handles new data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For most modern single-cell and large-scale workflows, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "UMAP has largely superseded t-SNE"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as the industry standard."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-SNE"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "nonlinear dimensionality reduction"}, {"type": "text", "text": " method for visualizing high-dimensional data in 2D/3D while preserving local structure."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It works by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "matching probability distributions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gaussian in high dimensions, t-distribution in low dimensions, minimizing KL divergence."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE excels at showing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "clusters and local relationships"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", but "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "distorts global structure"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (distances between clusters are not meaningful)."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "classical ML"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", t-SNE is used for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "exploratory data analysis and visualization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not as a predictive model."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "UMAP"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is faster, preserves more global structure, supports new data, and is often preferred in modern workflows, but t-SNE remains useful for fine-grain local granularity."}]}]}]}]}}